items.name: Skirt tug / dress tug / clothes tug
items.description:
LoRA trained to generate a character tugging their clothes to either cover the crotch or butt. It works with skirts, dresses, shirts, sweaters, etc.

Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it! And be sure to follow to check out the upcoming models.

Trigger (use one or more): clothes tug, skirt tug, dress tug, shirt tug, sweater tug

Ueful tags related to the tugging effect: clothes pull, skirt pull, dress pull, etc.

Other useful tags: wind, wind lift, skirt lift, dress lift, lifted by another, etc.

NSFW tags: panties, thong, ass, upskirt, pantyshot, implied pantyshot, etc.

Use multiple tags or increase their weight to amplify/modify the effect.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: Nishapur Splashware
items.description:
This model was trained on original examples of splashware pottery from the ancient city of Nishapur. The engraved details and splashes of brightly coloured glaze from these pieces translates to an organic, maximalist style that will add a rich beauty to your generations.

What is Nishapur splashware?

The technique of decorating pottery with splashes of coloured glaze was invented in Eighth-Century China, and by the Eleventh Century had spread along the Silk Road to the metropolis Nishapur in modern-day Iran. At the time, Nishapur was one of the largest and most prosperous cities on Earth, and it was here that the splashware technique was refined to include a layer of engraved detail underneath the glaze.

items.name: Alexander - Fate Grand Order
items.description:
Here's young Alexander, from Fate Grand Order

Guidelines and suggestions:

Recommended weight: Around 0.7

Optional tags: If you want his cape on, use the tags "cape", or "fur-trimmed cape" and "off the shoulder". If you want his cape off use "bare shoulders", or just don't prompt the cape, or if all else fails, throw it in the negative prompt.

If you are like me and don't like feet, prompt boots for his footwear and he's gonna show up wearing regular boots. But if you either want his regular outfit footwear or you like feet, prompt sandals or toeless footwear.

I'm actually impressed no one had done a lora on this character before. So, well, I took it upon myself to do it.

Such a cool character. And underappreciated too. And there is so much material from him out there. This was my lora with the biggest dataset so far. Though I goofed a bit in the parameters while making it, resulting in a slightly overfit model, it still has enough flexibility that we can play around with. Yet, if I feel it's too restrained, I can always come back to it later and release a new version.

So please tell me what you think!

(all of the above list can & should be used as triggers and weights)

It knows most common D&D races and it will produce some interesting great results when prompted correctly. (It has some minor issues with complicated races such as dragonborn & tieflings, etc. but you should be able to use a LORA to render these effectively. <3)

How to use

There is no embedded VAE but it was designed to be used with this:

☞ vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.ckpt

I also recommend using the following negatives:

EasyNegative or EasyNegativeV2 (The all around catch all. Always good in a bind)
badhandv4_anime (absolutely your go to neg for anime hands)
bad-hands-5 (good for the more realistic images but will not work amazingly for anime)
bad-artist \ bad-artist-anime (I’ve had good and bad luck)
bad_prompt \ bad_prompt_version2 (works very good sometimes)
(I typically use (bad-hands-5) & (bandhandv4_anime) at the same time to cover all bases.)


(Here are some example settings for you to start with, but please keep in mind YMMV!)

Steps: 30 = Sweet Spot / 10-150
Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ SDE Karras, Euler A, DDIM,
CFG scale: 4-11.5 = Sweet Spot / 4.5-15
Size: 512x768, 768x512, 640x840, 840x640, 600x896, 896x600, (any size)
Clip skip: 1
Hires Fix: Enabled
Upscale by: 1.5-2
Hires Steps: Equal to Half or Exact the exact amount of Steps (or higher)
Upscaler: Remacri Upscaler, Lollypop Upscaler, 4x_NMKD_DigArt_10k|
( I use DigArt 10k almost exclusively with everything except for 2D illustration & animation )

items.name: AlphaLyraeMerge
items.description:
Version 3 - This is the final version which adds an additional model to version 2 in order to solve the problem of not being able to create male subjects. I mixed in the BB Male Toon Mix model by ewolf to get the male characters. It does create male characters now, but sometimes they come out really effeminate. Still, that's not a bad thing depending on the image output you are looking for. The merge did remove some of the Anime Lineart Style Lora design from the final output, but I still think the design is close enough to be a good successor to Version 2.

Version 2 - This is an stylized model that mixes version 1 with my Anime Lineart Style Lora at 0.4 strength. It provides a different art style, but the model isn't able to create male subjects at all. I'm currently working on a version 3 which should allow for male subjects, but the style will end up being different since I'm merging a model designed specifically for male subjects into version 2.

This is a merged model of three Alpha Lyrae models: LyricED, AvaloriaED, and Terrane by EroticVibes. I loved the styles for all of these models and was curious what would happen if I merged them together. I like the images this model creates due to their unique style and mix of sexy and cartoony.

I've tested for NSFW and it works, though the images are a little too cartoony, so it almost looks like Rule 34 porn using western cartoons.

This model doesn't need a VAE. I've baked in Blessed2 VAE.

Note: version 1 and 2 don't work so well with male characters. I posted some sample images in the gallery for when I attempted to make fantasy images with the prompts for a muscular man and many of the images came out as effeminate men or simply as women. Haven't tried it with character loras, so it may be more successful at making male subjects using loras.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: Character Change - Fairy - A Friendly Guide in the Woods
items.description:
Adventure forth with your fairy companion! Your favorite character turns into a fairy to assist you on your quest.

This LyCORIS was created to turn your favorite characters into the faeries of ancient lore. It sadly can't seem to decide if the fairy is human-sized or tiny but I'm sure you can inpaint things to change that.

To use the LyCORIS, just give it a basic description or just combine it with other LoRA and LyCORIS along with the trigger words. I tested it with a few and it looks like it works with other human character LoRAs quite well. Just don't try turning Bowser into a fairy...

As you can see from the sample images provided, it's been tested on both realistic and anime models. Both result in giving off that fairy feel. It does alter clothes a bit but mostly focuses on giving your character fairy wings!

Trigger words are: fairy, wings

Additional words that might help: 1boy, 1girl, butterfly wings,

Recommended weight between 0.6-0.9.

, (masterpiece:1.2), best quality,PIXIV,taoist,
